#axiom separation of layers
logic != meme != story != tone

#axiom small core
keep core minimal and stable

#axiom append only logs
never delete or mutate raw logs

#axiom invariants are immutable
direction, gematria, core rules must not drift

#axiom validate before promote
generation is free, promotion requires proof

#axiom reproducible builds
every build must be replayable and identical

#axiom no hidden state mutation
state changes must be visible and traceable

#axiom one responsibility per unit
each function, file, or artifact has one purpose

#axiom reader first
optimize for human comprehension over cleverness

#axiom comments explain why
code shows what, comments explain why

#axiom reduce only with equivalence
shorter is valid only if behavior is unchanged

#axiom reject incomplete updates
partial definitions do not replace complete ones

#axiom map, do not replace
preserve multiple representations when needed

#axiom protect the core
if core drifts, system collapses

#axiom agents propose, human commits
no autonomous authority for critical changes

